Firewall: A fire wall is a network security system that monitors incoming and outgoing
network traffic based on a predetermined set of security rules. Barrier between trusted 
netork and untrusted network

SSL certificate: Enabled https protocol, more secure than https

Monitoring clients: monitor data from the server 

What are firewalls for
To avoid data breaches

Why is the traffic served over https?
So that the data is encrpyted then whole time.

What is monitoring used for
Getting data about running software and applications
